  "texts": [
    "CNNs, another type of LM, use convolutions, essentially filters, to analyze images or sequences of characters (Zrimec et al., 2020; Gao et al., 2022).",
    "These filters are employed to detect specific features or information within the input data.",
    "In plant biology, CNNs have been crucial for identifying regulatory enhancers in DNA and have been used in studying protein ubiquitination (Gao et al., 2022).",
    "However, like n-grams, CNNs have limitations due to the fixed size of their filters, making them better suited to capturing local patterns rather than understanding long-range dependencies or complex sentence structures (Zrimec et al., 2020).",
    "Despite these limitations, CNNs have performed well in the fields of genomics and phenomics."
  ],
